text-default.$description: Our default text color for most titles, tabs, and body text.

text-secondary.$description: Our secondary text color for inactive tabs, labels, timestamps, and other text that needs to be ‚Äúlighter‚Äù in order to create hierarchy.

text-tertiary.$description: Primarily used for placeholder text (for example in a search input), or for hierarchy below secondary text. Note that text at this level is below our color contrast threshold, and may not be readable to all users.

text-onbrand.$description: Used for text against a ‚Äúbackground with a fill color‚Äù (for example, a blue / purple background in our ‚ÄúShare‚Äù button)

text-brand.$description: Text that is tinted to match the current product, typically used for things like links. For specifically referring to concepts in design, we can use color-text-design instead.

text-assistive.$description: Pink text used when Figma is assisting you in some way (ex: in auto layout)

text-danger.$description: Red text used to alert users about an error.

text-warning.$description: Yellow text used to warn users about a potential problem.

icon-secondary.$description: Our secondary icon color for inactive elements that need to be ‚Äúlighter‚Äù in order to create hierarchy.

icon-tertiary.$description: Our tertiary icon color primarily used for carets

icon-onbrand.$description: Icons against a ‚Äúbackground with a fill color‚Äù (for example, a blue / purple background in our ‚ÄúShare‚Äù button)

icon-brand.$description: An icon tinted to match the accent color of the current product.

icon-assistive.$description: Pink icons used when Figma is assisting you in some way.

icon-danger.$description: Red icons used to alert users about an error.

icon-warning.$description: Yellow icons used to warn users about a potential problem.

icon-success.$description: Green icons used for confirmation, and approval.

bg-secondary.$description: Our secondary background color for most containers.

bg-hover.$description: A light grey hover fill color behind icons, and selectable elements.

bg-selected.$description: A lightly tinted selected fill color for selected elements.

bg-menu.$description: The dark fill color of our menus

bg-toolbar.$description: The dark fill color of our UI2 editor toolbar

bg-brand.$description: A fill tinted to match the accent color of the current product.

bg-figjam.$description: Purple fill color used for backgrounds like a button that opens in FigJam.

bg-handoff.$description: Green fill color used for backgrounds like a button that opens in Dev Mode.

bg-danger.$description: Red fill color behind destructive buttons, and error banners.

bg-warning.$description: Yellow fill color for warning banners

border-default.$description: Our default border color used as a divider between sections, or around inputs.

border-strong.$description: A much darker border color that we can use for emphasis around some UI elements.

border-onbrand-strong.$description: Used for borders against a bg-brand background

border-selected.$description: Default selection border color we use for focused / selected inputs.

border-selected-strong.$description: When presenting a selected border against an already selected background, we sometimes need to increase the prominence of the selected border.

border-menu.$description: Used for borders or dividers within a menu element.
